The fire raging on Table Mountain has largely been contained with no immediate threat to properties and people. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - The fire raging on Table Mountain has largely been contained with no immediate threat to properties and people. While the winds are still high, firefighters have extinguished a handful of hotspots on the mountain. The fire destroyed parts of the University of Cape Town and the Rhodes Memorial Restaurant when it broke out on Sunday morning. READ: Man arrested for Table Mountain fire A 35-year-old man has since been arrested. Cape Town Mayor Dan Plato says it's one of the most devastating wildfires to ever hit the Western Cape. eNCA reporter Lindsay Dentlinger shares more details in the video above.